        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:59PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Danbury, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danbury, Sherman, Brewster, Newtown, Ridgefield, Bethel, Brookfield,
New Fairfield, Redding, Putnam Lake, Brewster Hill, and Peach Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
